results.name: Number of series-reduced leaf-balanced rooted trees with n nodes. Number of orderless same-trees with n nodes and all leaves equal to 1.
comment: An unlabeled rooted tree is leaf-balanced if all branches from the same root have the same number of leaves. It is series-reduced if all positive out-degrees are greater than one.
